  "body": "A user made an error setting their mountPath - they set a docker-style mountpath `mountPath: /data/ldap/db:/var/lib/ldap`\n\nHowever, the error that they got (and inspection of the code) indicates that we just passed that straight through to docker (`API error (500): invalid mode for volumes-from: /var/lib/ldap`).  Docker treats the 3rd argument as a mode flag.\n\nWe should sanitize the input, both to help users when they make mistakes, but also because if Docker allowed other options in its mounts this could become a security issue.\n",
